  <statement>
    <p>
        Consider <m>f(x) = 0.1 x^2 - 1.1x + 3.4</m> and <m>g(x) = -0.5x^2 + 2.5x - 2</m>.  
    </p>

    <p>
      <ol marker="a.">
        <li>
          <p>
            Compute <m>f(3)</m>, <m>f'(3)</m>, <m>g(3)</m>, and <m>g'(3)</m>.  What do you observe?
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <p>
            Determine <m>L(x)</m>, the local linear approximation to <m>f(x)</m> at <m>x = 3</m>.  Explain why this function is also the local linear approximation to <m>g(x)</m> at <m>x = 3</m>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <p>
            Complete the following table of values for <m>f(x)</m>, <m>g(x)</m>, and <m>L(x)</m>:
